After Siena , we grabbed a train to Rome .

We even climbed the 551 steps to the top of the dome Michelangelo designed .
My favorite sculpture I saw was Michelangelo 's Pieta .
It 's of Mary holding Jesus ' limp body after his death .
He carved it out if one block of marble at the age of 24 .
He was famous in Florence , but no one had heard of him in Rome .
From what I hear , no one believed he made it , he was pissed about that , so he went back and chiseled his name across Mary 's chest .

I think Napoli translates to City where groups of fat 14 year - old girls walk around in clothing for 12 year - old skinny kids .
From my short time here I have discovered most of the guys here are mamas boys and the half of the population look like the people from Jersey Shore Show .

The people here are very colorful and most are nice if you engage them .
